"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-life-food-how-to-feed-15000-olympians-in-paris-start-with-baguettes\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Weekly recommendations for the best eats in town  Dishes that will be served to athletes at the Olympic Village  include falafel and fregola salad, and will include multicultural and vegetarian cuisines.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2255025382814674e-18, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: NYTIMES  PublishedJul 27, 2024, 02:00 PM  UpdatedJul 28, 2024, 12:29 AM  PARIS- The unforgettable moment when a competing athlete first enters the Olympic Village in Paris may be defined not by the complex's impressive size and sweep, but by a smell - the scent of freshly baked baguettes.\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 555, \"end\": 570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4085156388529468e-26, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.44635943276733e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is by design.\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 717, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Every French village has a bakery,\\\" said Mr Guillaume Thomas, who works in communications for the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 774, \"end\": 780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.9999703253780493, \"rank\": 2.629122683002436e-05, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We want people to be able to smell the baguette as they enter.\\\"\", \"from\": 834, \"to\": 898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A boulangerie set up at the mouth of the village will churn out more than 2,000 baguettes, croissants, pain au chocolat and focaccia daily, and even offer baking classes for athletes seeking respite from the gruelling competition.\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 1130, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the 15,000 Olympic athletes competing this summer, food is vital for optimising performance.\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The French would like to sprinkle in some delight.\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1233, \"end\": 1239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9284850856030684, \"rank\": 0.07702315196089368, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The centrepiece of the sprawling Olympic Village - once a power plant and then a film studio - is a network of six restaurants that will serve athletes around the clock.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, restaurants, or so the organisers call the places known as dining halls at past Olympics.\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was out of the question to call it anything else,\\\" said Mr Philipp Wurz, the food and beverage manager for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The building that houses the six athlete restaurants stands in the centre of the Olympic Village in Paris.\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1754, \"end\": 1769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4085156388529468e-26, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 1773, \"end\": 1778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.44635943276733e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: NYTIMES  At the end of a grand runway lined with flags from every delegation stands the 46,000 sq ft restaurant complex, with towering ceilings and imposing windows overlooking the Seine river.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1969, \"end\": 1974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4180298790950973e-16, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But inside, it looks a lot like a college cafeteria.\", \"from\": 1983, \"to\": 2035, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are cereal dispensers, soda fountains and buffet spreads among red floor tiles and kitschy decorations, like a colourful installation of pipes adorned with graffiti and cartoon eyes.\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2224, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Inside the building that houses the six athlete restaurants in the centre of the Olympic Village in Paris.\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2307, \"end\": 2322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4085156388529468e-26, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 2326, \"end\": 2331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.44635943276733e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: NYTIMES  What a college cafeteria does not have, though, are three chefs of famed French restaurants - Akrame Benallal, Amandine Chaignot and Alexandre Mazzia - who will prepare dishes such as coco beans with parsley ice cream and crispy mushroom croquettes.\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2423, \"end\": 2429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9284850856030684, \"rank\": 0.07702315196089368, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amandine_Chaignot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Amandine Chaignot\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amandine_Chaignot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amandine_Chaignot\"}, {\"begin\": 2550, \"end\": 2557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parsley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"parsley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parsley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parsley\"}, {\"begin\": 2558, \"end\": 2567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ice_cream\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0970610458396381e-63, \"text\": \"ice cream\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ice_cream\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ice_cream\"}, {\"begin\": 2579, \"end\": 2587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edible_mushroom\", \"score\": 0.9355535638630909, \"rank\": 0.0688858859887596, \"text\": \"mushroom\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edible_mushroom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edible_mushroom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The staff will wear polo T-shirts and gavroche caps.\", \"from\": 2601, \"to\": 2653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be cheese plates and French butter.\", \"from\": 2654, \"to\": 2700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2686, \"end\": 2692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9284850856030684, \"rank\": 0.07702315196089368, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The dishware is French porcelain, to be washed in three colossal dishwashers built for the Games.\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2717, \"end\": 2733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_porcelain\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French porcelain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_porcelain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_porcelain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A dish of coco beans with blackberries and parsley ice cream prepared by Amandine Chaignot, chef of the acclaimed Paris restaurant Pouliche.\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2873, \"end\": 2890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amandine_Chaignot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Amandine Chaignot\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amandine_Chaignot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amandine_Chaignot\"}, {\"begin\": 2914, \"end\": 2919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.44635943276733e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: NYTIMES  In late June, Sodexo Live, the French food-service company overseeing this operation, conducted a tasting for the media of the dizzying array of dishes to be served at the Olympic Village, including green gazpacho (refreshing), saffron risotto (vibrant and creamy), falafel (well-spiced but dry) and financiers (a tad too sweet).\", \"from\": 2942, \"to\": 3287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2972, \"end\": 2978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sodexo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\"}, {\"begin\": 2989, \"end\": 2995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9284850856030684, \"rank\": 0.07702315196089368, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is a difficult balance to strike between showcasing the French lifestyle and serving 40,000 meals a day that must cater to countless athletic, cultural and dietary requirements.\", \"from\": 3289, \"to\": 3476, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3355, \"end\": 3361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9284850856030684, \"rank\": 0.07702315196089368, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sodexo brought in 20 of its chefs from around the world to ensure cultural sensitivity in the six restaurants.\", \"from\": 3478, \"to\": 3588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3478, \"end\": 3484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sodexo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two of the restaurants are French, two are Asian, one is halal and one is simply called \\\"world\\\".\", \"from\": 3589, \"to\": 3685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Carole Galissant, who works in nutrition at Sodexo Live, coordinated with nutritionists from each delegation to ensure specific needs were met.\", \"from\": 3687, \"to\": 3833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3734, \"end\": 3740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sodexo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Koreans wanted kimchi.\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 3860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3838, \"end\": 3845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koreans\", \"score\": 0.999697069580674, \"rank\": 0.0002347014715899859, \"text\": \"Koreans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koreans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koreans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Japanese wanted miso.\", \"from\": 3861, \"to\": 3886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3865, \"end\": 3873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_cuisine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.633517097265877e-41, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_cuisine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_cuisine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not all requests could be fulfilled.\", \"from\": 3888, \"to\": 3924, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Several Caribbean nations asked for passion fruit, but sustainability regulations for the Games prohibit importing ingredients by air.\", \"from\": 3925, \"to\": 4059, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are still placing a special focus on the French recipes,\\\" Ms Galissant said.\", \"from\": 4061, \"to\": 4141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4106, \"end\": 4112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9284850856030684, \"rank\": 0.07702315196089368, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Blanquette de veau, lemon tart, Paris-Brest.\\\"\", \"from\": 4142, \"to\": 4188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4175, \"end\": 4186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Brest\", \"score\": 0.8020135056820301, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris-Brest\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Brest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Brest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But many athletes may never get to try those dishes.\", \"from\": 4190, \"to\": 4242, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The rule of thumb is to try to stick to what is familiar as much as possible and minimise the new,\\\" said nutritionist Purity Kamande for the Kenyan Olympic team.\", \"from\": 4244, \"to\": 4406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4386, \"end\": 4405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenyan Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Because we know that with the new, all these issues could come and affect them.\\\"\", \"from\": 4407, \"to\": 4488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With that in mind, she is shipping a package to Paris containing Kenyan comforts like ugali, a carbohydrate-heavy cornmeal, and Kericho Gold tea.\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4538, \"end\": 4543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.44635943276733e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4618, \"end\": 4630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kericho_Gold\", \"score\": 0.9999999328647413, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kericho Gold\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kericho_Gold\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kericho_Gold\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Shawn Hueglin, a senior sports dietitian for the United States Olympic Committee, said the Americans mailed protein shakes, pretzels, popcorn, jerky, energy bars and, of course, peanut butter for their athletes.\", \"from\": 4637, \"to\": 4851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4689, \"end\": 4720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_&_Paralympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"United States Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_&_Paralympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_&_Paralympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Hueglin, who has worked at four Summer Olympics, said the host country will sometimes focus on promoting its cuisine at the expense of meeting athletes' performance needs.\", \"from\": 4853, \"to\": 5027, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While she appreciated that the dining hall at the 2021 Tokyo Olympics served food from every region of Japan, \\\"they were not the best options for athletes to grab before they went to compete\\\", she said.\", \"from\": 5028, \"to\": 5230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5131, \"end\": 5136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999054126, \"rank\": 9.43005009761451e-11, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Sharon Madigan, who oversees nutrition for the Irish Olympic team, has a different perspective.\", \"from\": 5232, \"to\": 5330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5235, \"end\": 5241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharon_Watts\", \"score\": 0.750137752839975, \"rank\": 0.3330884843121379, \"text\": \"Sharon\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharon_Watts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sharon_Watts\"}, {\"begin\": 5242, \"end\": 5249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Madigan\", \"score\": 0.9999999927476892, \"rank\": 7.252237962162183e-09, \"text\": \"Madigan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Madigan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Madigan\"}, {\"begin\": 5282, \"end\": 5287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"score\": 0.6341742655176963, \"rank\": 0.5423496452234018, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These are great opportunities for athletes who may not have a wide palate to try foods that they would not usually have, and like them and enjoy them,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 5331, \"to\": 5493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With one caveat - the Irish need their porridge.\", \"from\": 5495, \"to\": 5543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5517, \"end\": 5522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"score\": 0.6341742655176963, \"rank\": 0.5423496452234018, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Porridge is something that the French really do not do very well, or do not do at all,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 5544, \"to\": 5642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5576, \"end\": 5582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9284850856030684, \"rank\": 0.07702315196089368, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are bringing oats.\", \"from\": 5643, \"to\": 5665, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lots of it.\\\"\", \"from\": 5666, \"to\": 5678, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Madigan said her athletes were excited to socialise in the Olympic Village restaurants, especially after the limited communal dining in Tokyo, during the Covid-19 pandemic.\", \"from\": 5680, \"to\": 5855, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5683, \"end\": 5690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Madigan\", \"score\": 0.9999999927476892, \"rank\": 7.252237962162183e-09, \"text\": \"Madigan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Madigan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Madigan\"}, {\"begin\": 5742, \"end\": 5757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4085156388529468e-26, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 5819, \"end\": 5824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999958169079216, \"rank\": 4.170796531191175e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thankfully, the French are very familiar with the art of gathering.\", \"from\": 5856, \"to\": 5923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5872, \"end\": 5878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9284850856030684, \"rank\": 0.07702315196089368, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Here in France, we talk about conviviality, about eating together, and that is also an element of an athlete's performance,\\\" said Ms Galissant.\", \"from\": 5925, \"to\": 6069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5934, \"end\": 5940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8485865834401395e-18, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Brice Guyart, a two-time Olympic gold medallist who now works for the Games, consulted past and current Olympians in helping to create the Village experience.\", \"from\": 6071, \"to\": 6232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6074, \"end\": 6086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brice_Guyart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brice Guyart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brice_Guyart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brice_Guyart\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: NYTIMES  French athlete Brice Guyart, a two-time gold medallist in fencing who has been consulting with athletes to help fine-tune their experience at the Paris Olympics, said he has always loved that everyone at the Games can eat in one place, no matter the athlete or nation.\", \"from\": 6234, \"to\": 6518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6250, \"end\": 6256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9284850856030684, \"rank\": 0.07702315196089368, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 6265, \"end\": 6277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brice_Guyart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brice Guyart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brice_Guyart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brice_Guyart\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 2000 Olympics in Sydney, he went to the dining hall at 1am right after winning the gold and befriended Mr Shinichi Shinohara, a Japanese silver medallist in judo.\", \"from\": 6520, \"to\": 6689, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6544, \"end\": 6550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.999999999915417, \"rank\": 8.464738458755826e-11, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 6633, \"end\": 6651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shinichi_Shinohara\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shinichi Shinohara\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shinichi_Shinohara\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shinichi_Shinohara\"}, {\"begin\": 6655, \"end\": 6663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_cuisine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.633517097265877e-41, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_cuisine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_cuisine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Guyart had several requests for the Sodexo Live team based on his experiences.\", \"from\": 6691, \"to\": 6772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6730, \"end\": 6736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sodexo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not make the plates too big or the athletes will overeat.\", \"from\": 6773, \"to\": 6833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Keep the temperature moderate, as diners at the Sydney and Athens Olympics had to wear coats in the cafeterias.\", \"from\": 6834, \"to\": 6945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6882, \"end\": 6888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.999999999915417, \"rank\": 8.464738458755826e-11, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 6893, \"end\": 6899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.9997093323196232, \"rank\": 0.0002907521913477431, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also suggested that the chefs prepare cakes for athletes celebrating birthdays.\", \"from\": 6946, \"to\": 7028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's the little things,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 7030, \"to\": 7064, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Guyart said along with winning gold in Athens, he fondly remembers the Greek salad at the cafeteria, with fresh cucumbers and tomatoes, and big chunks of briny feta.\", \"from\": 7066, \"to\": 7234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7108, \"end\": 7114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.9997093323196232, \"rank\": 0.0002907521913477431, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 7140, \"end\": 7151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_salad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Greek salad\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_salad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_salad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's my Proust madeleine,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 7235, \"to\": 7273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chef Benallal, one of the restaurant chefs cooking at the Village, is hoping he can conjure up some similarly evocative moments for the Paris athletes.\", \"from\": 7275, \"to\": 7426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7411, \"end\": 7416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.44635943276733e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They for sure have nutritional needs,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 7428, \"to\": 7476, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But also, maybe sometimes, they can have pleasure.\", \"from\": 7477, \"to\": 7528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"NYTIMES  Food and drink  Olympics 2024  Chefs  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 7528, \"to\": 7691, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 7692, \"to\": 7706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 7708, \"to\": 7725, \"entities\": []}]}"